\,\color{#c00}{4+4 = 9}\,
\,5 + 5 = 10.\,
\,\color{#c00}n\,
\,n+1.\,
\begin{array}{cccccccc}\ldots & \ 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 &\ldots \\ \color{#c00}\ldots & \color{#c00}{-1} & \color{#c00}0 & \color{#c00}1 & \color{#c00}2 & \color{#c00}3 & \color{#c00}4 &\ldots\end{array}
\begin{eqnarray}{\rm Generally\ we\ have\ that}\quad  \color{#c00}{a+b}&\,=\,& (a+1)+(b+1)-1\,=\, a+b+1\\ \color{#c00}{a\,*b}&\,=\,& (a+1)\,*(b+1)-1\,=\, a\,*\,b+a+b\end{eqnarray}
4 \equiv 0
4 + 4 \equiv 0
9 \equiv 0
4+4 \equiv 9
a\star b=a+b+1
4\star 4=9
